{"name":"Der Geflugesalat","permission":{"default":0,"eKM9nHTr2M2uSgUw":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-eureka":{"initialization-folder":"Der Geflugesalat"}},"content":"<p>The house is a fairly large one on the outskirts of the city and it has some very obvious, and very unusual, features. From the roof a large iron pole projects skywards and another part of the roof is flat, so that it could easily be stood on. Also built onto the roof is a tall, wooden tower-like structure supporting a wide platform. This is nearly as tall as the iron pole.&nbsp;</p>","img":"modules/wfrp4e-eureka/assets/images/icons/logo.png","_id":"l0AUiwgSymQNbK5v"}
{"name":"The Shed","permission":{"default":0,"eKM9nHTr2M2uSgUw":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-eureka":{"initialization-folder":"Der Geflugesalat"}},"content":"<p>Inside, and down some stairs, is the entrance to the secret workshop of @Actor[Wolfgang Kugelschreiber]{Wolfgang Kugelschreiber}...&nbsp;</p>","img":"modules/wfrp4e-eureka/assets/images/icons/logo.png","_id":"VEhcFMtqAq7sIJk1"}
{"name":"Inside The House","permission":{"default":0,"eKM9nHTr2M2uSgUw":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-eureka":{"initialization-folder":"Der Geflugesalat"}},"content":"<p>Fatboy will take the Characters into the neat and tidy house, but he cannot find the inventor. Muttering to himself: <em>&ldquo;The old fool&rsquo;s down there again, I'll be bound...</em>&rdquo;, he will take the Characters out to a shed behind the house.</p>","img":"modules/wfrp4e-eureka/assets/images/icons/logo.png","_id":"9Ml1qXxGVBDKWIz4"}
{"name":"Doorbells","permission":{"default":0,"eKM9nHTr2M2uSgUw":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-eureka":{"initialization-folder":"Der Geflugesalat"}},"content":"<p>The large double door has a heavy rope hanging down at one side of it. A sign next to the rope reads <em>&ldquo;Pull this please.&rdquo; </em>If the Characters take the advice of the sign, a series of bells will play a merry tune over and over again.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Suddenly, there is a loud bang from behind the door. One of them is opened by a halfling carrying a hammer. He mutters something about<em> &ldquo;Damn bells!&rdquo;</em> and then asks the Characters what they want. <em>&ldquo;Just what do you think you are doing, ringing bells like that? Hmm? Well?&rdquo;&nbsp;</em></p>\n<p>If the Characters mention that Uwe sent them, then the halfling&rsquo;s attitude will change completely. Smiling, he will beckon them into the house.&nbsp;</p>","img":"modules/wfrp4e-eureka/assets/images/icons/logo.png","_id":"vEAQUkJ8YIchud5P"}
{"name":"Laboratory","permission":{"default":0,"eKM9nHTr2M2uSgUw":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-eureka":{"initialization-folder":"Der Geflugesalat"}},"content":"<h1>Laboratory</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Inside and down, the workshop (unlike the house) is a mess. Chemicals bubble in strange vats and bottles, and gurgle through twisty glasswear. Obscure mechanical devices little the floor in various stages of completion &ndash; or have they been partly dismantled? Bits of firearm are scattered about the place, along with small piles of gunpowder. It&rsquo;s a workshop, laboratory, smithy, alchemist&rsquo;s lair and smell factory all crammed into a pint pot.</p>","img":"modules/wfrp4e-eureka/assets/images/icons/logo.png","_id":"D1S9Y72DO6wJ5yxb"}
{"name":"Kugelmatic Underwater Ship","permission":{"default":0,"eKM9nHTr2M2uSgUw":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-eureka":{"initialization-folder":"Inventions"}},"content":"<h1>Kugelmatic Underwater Ship</h1>\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3><em>\"Ze localz zink eet's a metal vog octopus!\"</em></h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In the centre of all the confusion is a large object covered by a sheet. As the Characters enter, a man appears from under it. His hair is grey and unkempt, and his eyes are wide, bloodshot and have a manic look to them. This is Wolfgang Kugelschreiber.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The underwater ship is a 2 seater submersible that currently only @Actor[Wolfgang Kugelschreiber]{Kugelschreiber} and @Actor[Ferwin \"Fatboy\" Smallnose]{Fatboy} can pilot.</p>","img":"modules/wfrp4e-eureka/assets/images/icons/logo.png","_id":"MpuHRcIhRGy1dReL"}
{"name":"Kugelmatic Chicken and Turkey Plucker","permission":{"default":0,"eKM9nHTr2M2uSgUw":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-eureka":{"initialization-folder":"Inventions"}},"content":"<h1>Kugelmatic Chicken and Turkey Plucker</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><em>\"Zis device is ze poultry in motion!\"</em></h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Designed as a cage and series of shaving razors and mechanical hands and blades controlled by levers that supposedly shave the unlucky poutlry. It is best not to ask too much about how successful these devices are lest fowl play have been involved. No turkeys or chickens have plucked up the courage to attest to its success, meaning the Professor has probably been an unlucky plucker so far. It is probably for the best Kugelschreiber has gone cold turkey on using it recently. Thankfully it only cost him a poultry sum to build.</p>","img":"modules/wfrp4e-eureka/assets/images/icons/logo.png","_id":"0QVmklCdKmkbBlqf"}
{"name":"Kugelmatic Underwater Breathing Device","permission":{"default":0,"eKM9nHTr2M2uSgUw":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-eureka":{"initialization-folder":"Inventions"}},"content":"<h1>Kugelmatic Underwater Breathing Device</h1>\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3><em>\"One previous careless owner. If you zee him down zere, pay no attenzion!\"</em></h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Kugelmatic Underwater Breathing Device is essentially a primitive snorkel, which does, due to its simple design, actually work quite well. This could be useful to a Character that wishes to escape Kugelschreiber's house by swimming; for example, following Kugelschreiber and his Underwatership into the canal.</p>","img":"modules/wfrp4e-eureka/assets/images/icons/logo.png","_id":"6E0OLhIR0h8K3QZc"}
{"name":"Kugelmatic Fire Extinguisher","permission":{"default":0,"eKM9nHTr2M2uSgUw":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-eureka":{"initialization-folder":"Inventions"}},"content":"<h1>Kugelmatic Fire Extinguisher</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><em>\"Eet stickz ze fire een place!\"</em></h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Kugelmatic Mobile Fire Extinguisher is a wheeled trolley with a key, a pump and a hose attached. When the pump is used, brown and smelly chemically-treated water shoots out of the hose. This will extinguish any fire it comes in contact with in exactly the same fashion as ordinary water but the gloop will also stick to anyone it hits.</p>\n<p>It requires two operators (one to pump and one to aim the hose). It has enough fluid for three uses.</p>\n<p>The Character pumping must make an <strong>Average (+20) Athletics</strong> Test to indicate the vigour with which they pump.</p>\n<p>The Character aiming must make a <strong>Ranged (Engineering) </strong>Test, and if that test is failed use the Scatter rules on WFRP page 163 to determine where the Character actually manages to spray the extinguisher fluid.</p>\n<p>The range of the Kugelmatic Mobile Fire Extinguisher is 4 yards and it has a <em>Blast</em> Quality of 4. Any target within the Blast take no damage, but instead gain one <em>Entangled </em>Condition with a Strength of 30 with +10 Strength per SL of the pumping <strong>Athletics </strong>Test. For every +2 SL the <strong>Ranged (Engineering)</strong> Test was passed by targets gain +1 additional <em>Entangled </em>Condition.</p>","img":"modules/wfrp4e-eureka/assets/images/icons/logo.png","_id":"QjjYt1ZSGOAwkONG"}
{"name":"Kugelmatic Fast Draw Scabbard","permission":{"default":0,"eKM9nHTr2M2uSgUw":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-eureka":{"initialization-folder":"Inventions"}},"content":"<h1>Kugelmatic Fast Draw Scabbard</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><em>\"Zis vill put a zpring in your zwordplay, guaranteed!\"</em></h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This is a scabbard (for a sword represented as a Hand Weapon only) with a spring device in the bottom of it. When the device works correctly (on a roll of 6+ on a d10), then the sword shoots out into the user's hand and for the wielder's attacks with the sword have the Fast Quality for 1 Round.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>When the Kugelmatic Fast Draw Scabbard malfunctions then the sword shoots out of the scabbard and lands @roll[1d10]{1d10 yards away}. This might distract the opponent with fits of laughter on a good day. On a bad day it leaves it wielder without a sword.</p>","img":"modules/wfrp4e-eureka/assets/images/icons/logo.png","_id":"MshQXFthC465wS8l"}
